main event: Two witnesses reported seeing a bright object moving across the sky in Manahawkin, New Jersey, on June 15, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared to hover for a moment before speeding away,The color of the object was described as dull grayish-white,The witnesses noted that the object did not resemble any conventional aircraft,They believed they saw a vapor trail after the object disappeared,The observation lasted for approximately 2 minutes.
witness description: The witnesses described the object as moving at moderate speed without sound or visible propulsion.
